msgid "The Song of the Alchemists"
"\n"
"\nBy Marobar Sul"
"\n"
"\n"
"\nWhen King Maraneon's alchemist had to leave his station"
"\n"
"\nAfter a laboratory experiment that yielded detonation,"
"\n"
"\nThe word went out that the King did want"
"\n"
"\nA new savant"
"\n"
"\nTo mix his potions and brews."
"\n"
"\nBut he declared he would only choose"
"\n"
"\nA fellow who knew the tricks and the tools."
"\n"
"\nThe King refused to hire on more fools."
"\n"
"\nAfter much deliberation, discussions, and debates,"
"\n"
"\nThe King picked two well-learned candidates."
"\n"
"\nIanthippus Minthurk and Umphatic Faer,"
"\n"
"\nAn ambitious pair,"
"\n"
"\nVied to prove which one was the best."
"\n"
"\nSaid the King, "There will be a test.""
"\n"
"\nThey went to a large chamber with herbs, gems, tomes,"
"\n"
"\nPots, measuring cups, all under high crystalline domes."
"\n"
"\n"Make me a tonic that will make me invisible,""
"\n"
"\nLaughed the King in a tone some would call risible."
"\n"
"\nSo Umphatic Faer and Ianthippus Minthurk"
"\n"
"\nBegan to work,"
"\n"
"\nMincing herbs, mashing metal, refining strange oils,"
"\n"
"\nCautiously setting their cauldrons to burbling boils,"
"\n"
"\nEach on his own, sending mixing bowls mixing,"
"\n"
"\nSometimes peeking to see what the other was fixing."
"\n"
"\nAfter they had worked for nearly three-quarters an hour,"
"\n"
"\nBoth Ianthippus Minthurk and Umphatic Faer"
"\n"
"\nWinked at the other, certain he won."
"\n"
"\nSaid King Maraneon,"
"\n"
"\n"Now you must taste the potions you've wrought,"
"\n"
"\nTake a spoon and sample it right from your pot.""
"\n"
"\nMinthurk vanished as his lips touched his brew,"
"\n"
"\nBut Faer tasted his and remained apparent in view."
"\n"
"\n"You think you mixed silver, blue diamonds, and yellow grass!""
"\n"
"\nThe King laughed, "Look up, Faer, up to the ceiling glass."
"\n"
"\nThe light falling makes the ingredients you choose"
"\n"
"\nQuite different hues.""
"\n"
"\n"What do you get," asked the floating voice, bold,"
"\n"
"\n"Of a potion of red diamonds, blue grass, and gold?""
"\n"
"\n"By [Dwemer God]," said Faer, his face in a wince,"
"\n"
"\n"I've made a potion to fortify my own intelligence.""
msgstr "錬金術師の詩歌\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nマロバー・サル著\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nマラネオ国王おかかえの錬金術師が持ち場を去った\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n研究所での実験中に爆発事故を起こしたからだ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n国王のおふれが回された\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n新しい術師を募集する\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n薬や何かを混ぜるのだ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n王が選ぶと決めたのは\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n術と道具を使えるものだけ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n愚かな術師はもうたくさん\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n検討、会議、話し合い\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n王は候補を2人に決めた\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nイアンスィップス・ミンサークとウンファティック・ファー\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nどちらもとにかく野心でいっぱい\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nどちらがすごいか競うのだ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n王は「試験を行う」と\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n薬草、宝石、書物にお鍋、計量カップを用意した\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n透明ドームの屋根の下、部屋に2人は通された\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「飲むと姿が見えなくなる薬を作り出せ」\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n笑い上戸の王様はやっぱり笑ってこう言った\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nイアンスィップス・ミンサークとウンファティック・ファー\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n2人は作業に取り掛かる\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n薬草刻んで金属溶かし、奇妙なオイルを精製し\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n釜に入れたら温めて用心深く泡立たす\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n中身を鉢に移したら混ぜて混ぜて混ぜまくる\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n時々互いを盗み見て、相手の様子を確認し\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n45分も経ったころ、\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nイアンスィップス・ミンサークとウンファティック・ファー\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nどっちも自分が勝ったと思い、相手にウィンクしてやった\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nマラネオ国王こう言った\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「それでは今から自分たちの作った薬を飲んでみろ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n鍋から一さじすくい取り味見をして見せてくれ」\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nミンサークが薬を口にするやいなや彼の姿は消え失せた\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nファーも味見をしてみたが、彼の姿はそのままだった\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「銀とブルーダイヤモンドと黄色の草をちゃんと混ぜたと思うのか？」\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n王は笑って教えてやった。「見てみろガラスの天井だ\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n光がお前を惑わせて使うべきだった材料の\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n色を変えてしまったのだ」\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「ところで何を混ぜたのかな」浮かれてうるさい声がたずねた\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「レッド・ダイヤモンドと青い草、それに金ではないのかな？」\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「(ドゥエマーの神の名前)の力によって」ファーは若干おびえて言った\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n「私は自分の知能を高める薬を作りました」"

