#: 21337012-0-2954
msgctxt "21337012-0-2954"
msgid "It was a chill, moonless Tirdas night,"
"\nWhen on my window did alight,"
"\nA humble torchbug all aglow,"
"\nWho, passing by, thought to say hello."
"\n"
"\n"How do you fare?" I did ask."
"\nAs in his light, my face did bask."
"\n"Well and better still," said he,"
"\n"Though I had to leave my humble tree.""
"\n"
"\nI thought that was sad and so I said,"
"\n"Where will you now rest your sleepy head?""
"\nImagined I, that it was shelter he did seek,"
"\nBut as a bug, he was asking meek."
"\n"
"\n"I leave tonight for southern shores,"
"\n Where I will winter in due course.""
"\nThen before I could stammer a reply,"
"\nHe was aloft, flying away into the sky."
"\n"
"\nSo I pondered to myself alone:"
"\nHere I thought he lost his home,"
"\nAnd upon my abode, he looked with envy,"
"\nBut in the end, the jealous one was me."
msgstr "冷たい月のない火耀の夜\\r"
